  ogImage="/assets/og.png"
  ogType="article"
  breadcrumbs={[{"name": "Home", "href": "/"}, {"name": "Docs", "href": "/docs/"}, {"name": "Tools", "href": "/docs/tools/"}, {"name": "Code intelligence", "href": "/docs/tools/code-intel.html"}]}
>
<header class="doc-page-header">
  <span class="eyebrow">Tools &middot; Code intelligence</span>
    <h1 style="margin-top:1rem;"><em>Code intelligence</em> tools</h1>
    <p class="doc-hero__sub">
      The toolkit for asking concrete code questions — what's the
      shape of this repo, where is symbol X, who imports file Y, what
      AST patterns match, what's actually on disk right now, and what
      changed-file impact the agent should verify next.
    </p>
</header>
<section class="section">
  <div class="container">
    <article class="doc-body" style="max-width: 78ch;">

      <article id="repo_map">
        <h2><code>repo_map</code> <span style="color:var(--acid); font-size:0.7em;">read</span></h2>
        <p>Token-budgeted aider-style outline of ranked files and key symbols.</p>
        <h3>When to use it</h3>
        <p>Onboarding the agent to an unfamiliar repo. Returns a high-signal map at a fixed token budget instead of a directory listing.</p>
        <h3>Input</h3>
        <pre><code>&lcub; "budgetTokens": 4000 &rcub;</code></pre>
      </article>

      <article id="cross_search">
        <h2><code>cross_search</code> <span style="color:var(--acid); font-size:0.7em;">read</span></h2>
        <p>Search one term across code chunks, schema objects, RPC/trigger bodies, routes, and memories.</p>
        <h3>When to use it</h3>
        <p>Broad indexed search when you want to know everywhere a name appears — not just in app code, but in DB and Reef memories too. Use <code>verbosity: "compact"</code> on noisy hits.</p>
        <h3>Input</h3>
        <pre><code>&lcub; "term": "admin_audit_log", "limit": 20 &rcub;</code></pre>
      </article>

      <article id="ast_find_pattern">
        <h2><code>ast_find_pattern</code> <span style="color:var(--acid); font-size:0.7em;">read</span></h2>
        <p>Run ast-grep structural search over fresh indexed JS/TS/JSX/TSX files.</p>
        <h3>When to use it</h3>
        <p>When you need real call sites, not text matches. Catches defaulted exports, dynamic imports, and patterns grep can't see. In TSX, object-literal or JSX-ambiguous patterns are auto-anchored when needed, so <code>&lcub; ssr: false &rcub;</code> can still match as an expression-shaped pattern.</p>
        <h3>Input</h3>
        <pre><code>&lcub;
  "pattern":   "supabase.from($TABLE)",
  "languages": ["ts", "tsx"],
  "pathGlob":  "app/**/*.tsx",
  "maxMatches": 200
&rcub;</code></pre>
      </article>

      <article id="live_text_search">
        <h2><code>live_text_search</code> <span style="color:var(--acid); font-size:0.7em;">read</span></h2>
        <p>Live ripgrep over the working tree for exact disk text. Defaults to fixed-string search.</p>
        <h3>When to use it</h3>
        <p>After edits. The daemon usually catches up indexed facts in the background, but <code>live_text_search</code> reads from the current filesystem immediately.</p>
        <h3>Input</h3>
        <pre><code>&lcub;
  "query":      "verifySession(",
  "pathGlob":   "lib/**/*.ts",
  "fixedStrings": true,
  "maxMatches": 100
&rcub;</code></pre>
      </article>

      <article id="symbols_of">
        <h2><code>symbols_of</code> <span style="color:var(--acid); font-size:0.7em;">read</span></h2>
        <p>List indexed symbols declared in a file.</p>
        <h3>When to use it</h3>
        <p>Quick way to learn what a file exposes without re-reading the file.</p>
      </article>

      <article id="imports_impact">
        <h2><code>imports_impact</code> <span style="color:var(--acid); font-size:0.7em;">read</span></h2>
        <p>Trace indexed files that depend on a file.</p>
        <h3>When to use it</h3>
        <p>Before any rename or breaking change. Returns the import graph of dependents — including barrel re-exports.</p>
        <h3>Input</h3>
        <pre><code>&lcub; "filePath": "lib/users/queries.ts", "limit": 200 &rcub;</code></pre>
        <p>See <a href="../recipes/safe-refactoring.html">How to refactor safely</a> for the full workflow.</p>
      </article>

      <article id="reef_diff_impact">
        <h2><code>reef_diff_impact</code> <span style="color:var(--acid); font-size:0.7em;">read</span></h2>
        <p>Changed-file impact composer for the current working tree.</p>
        <h3>When to use it</h3>
        <p>After edits and before final diagnostics. It combines changed files, indexed import edges, related findings, and conventions so the agent can see which callers or rules may need another look.</p>
        <h3>Input</h3>
        <pre><code>&lcub; "filePaths": ["lib/users/queries.ts", "lib/users/index.ts"] &rcub;</code></pre>
      </article>

      <article id="imports_hotspots">
        <h2><code>imports_hotspots</code> <span style="color:var(--acid); font-size:0.7em;">read</span></h2>
        <p>Most widely-imported files in the project.</p>
        <h3>When to use it</h3>
        <p>"Where does the most damage start?" — refactoring centrality.</p>
      </article>

      <article id="imports_cycles">
        <h2><code>imports_cycles</code> <span style="color:var(--acid); font-size:0.7em;">read</span></h2>
        <p>Detect circular imports across the indexed module graph.</p>
      </article>

      <article id="exports_of">
        <h2><code>exports_of</code> <span style="color:var(--acid); font-size:0.7em;">read</span></h2>
        <p>List exports surfaced by a file. Useful as a preflight before editing the file's public surface.</p>
      </article>

      <article id="imports_deps">
        <h2><code>imports_deps</code> <span style="color:var(--acid); font-size:0.7em;">read</span></h2>
        <p>What this file imports, and from where. Inverse of <code>imports_impact</code>.</p>
      </article>

